For example, singing on stage together, speaking Japanese, it's so scary! You just got to try your best...

354
00:29:09,540 --> 00:29:13,040
...throw your fears away. 怖くないよ。
...throw your fears away. It's not scary.

355
00:29:13,040 --> 00:29:15,540
How do you overcome? It's so scary!

356
00:29:15,540 --> 00:29:20,040
We just sang Brave Shine! Brave Shine! We just sang, so...

357
00:29:20,040 --> 00:29:22,540
It's such a good song, it's very fitting.

358
00:29:22,540 --> 00:29:30,040
Right? Yeah, fight your fears! 怖くないね。勇気持って。Courage. And, yeah, challenge your dreams!
Right? Yeah, fight your fears! It's not scary. Have courage. Courage. And, yeah, challenge your dreams!

359
00:29:30,040 --> 00:29:35,540
Yeah, but fears are also part of our lives, right? Like, maybe if we're not... if we don't feel the fear, then...

360
00:29:35,540 --> 00:29:40,040
how can we overcome? Like, how can we do... how to say... how can we do...

361
00:29:40,040 --> 00:29:46,540
I don't know the word... like...

362
00:29:46,540 --> 00:29:48,540
How can we challenge our past selves?

363
00:29:48,540 --> 00:29:53,040
How can we challenge ourselves and do our best every single day, right?

364
